1) What is Selenium

-> It is a framework / Set of Libraries / Project / API used to test web-based testing.
-> It can be used with multiple languages. - Java - .jar, C# - .dll, PHP, Phyton
-> Selenium won't support desktop based applications.
-> Selenium is open source
-> Selenium supports multiple browsers - Firefox, Chrome, Safari
-> Selenium supports on multi platform support - Windows, Linux, MacOS
-> Selenium components -> IDE, RC, Grid, WebDriver
-> Selenium v1.0 -> IDE + RC + Grid 1
-> Selenium v2.0 -> Grid 2 + WebDriver + RC (Last Version 2.35.1)
-> Selenium v3.0 -> 3.141.59 (3 is the version and 141.59 is the build) - WebDriver + W3C Specification + Grid 3
-> Selenium new website - https://www.selenium.dev
-> Selenium v3.0 is a W3C recommendation. W3C is an inteernational community that works to develop Web Standards.

2) Automation testing

-> Web Based Testing -> Selenium / QTP / UFT
-> Desktop based - > QTP
-> Database App -> SQl, MySQL, Hadoop
-> Mobile App -> Robotium (Android), Calabash (iOS), Appium (Both Android & iOS)
-> Web Services REST / SOAP -> POSTMAN, SOAP UI


3) Selenium is an API

-> E.g. I am a Java Devloper. I deigned 'Calculator' class which support add, sub, mul, div etc.

public Calculator {

public static void main(String[] args)
{
  Calculator obj = new Calculator(); // What is an Object? (new Calculator()) and obj is reference variable holding value of Object
  obj.add();
  obj.div();
  obj.sub();
  obj.multi();
}

